narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: German's an excellent class, of course if you want to actually learn German. It's demanding, but not unreasonably so.
I would recommend shopping all available TAs, as it makes all the difference.

German 120 with Jason Kavett is definitely a rewarding class, especially for those looking for a good balance between grammar/vocabulary and learning about the cultural aspects. The atmosphere of the class is very friendly and relaxed, creating an setting in which students felt comfortable asking questions when unclear about a concept or simply to further inquire about something about German culture.
If you want to take German, you should take L2 also...
Yes, I would recommend this class for another student because it finishes off the basic rules needed for speaking in German. The rest is just memorization.
